<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1532,1557]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named for the adpressed teeth or teeth touching, in contact with the shaft, verb and noun in apposition in Greek, 
<emphasis box="[386,464,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">thigma</emphasis>
, touch, and 
<emphasis box="[601,684,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">akaina,</emphasis>
tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1604,1629]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[276,502,1604,1629]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">female and nymph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[518,585,1604,1629]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Color</emphasis>
. Crown short, with two pairs of small wedge-shaped dark brown marking apically and subapically respectively, transverse faint orange line medially (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1092,1639,1664]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d). Pronotum with two pairs of brown to dark brown spots near compound eye (
<figureCitation box="[731,817,1676,1701]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d). Tegmina with many dark brown reticulate colour patterns and some recurved vein-like markings in costal cells (
<figureCitation box="[870,957,1711,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–d). Nymph stramineous, with two basal abdominal segments brown (
<figureCitation box="[474,571,1748,1773]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,194,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1902]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 12a–i. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., habitus, dorsally. a. Wiedouw, male; b. Gifberg, female; c. Wiedouw, female; d. Gifberg, male; e. Nymph, Gifberg; f, hind wing, male; g, tegmina, male; h, hind wing female; i, tegmina, female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626835/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1783,1808]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,450,1783,1808]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity box="[636,804,1783,1808]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.525" metricValueMax="4.65" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="4.525" valueMax="4.65" valueMin="4.4">4.40–4.65 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity box="[973,1141,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="0.39" valueMax="0.41" valueMin="0.37">0.37–0.41 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity box="[151,322,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.5999999999999996" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="0.375" valueMax="0.39" valueMin="0.36">0.36–0.39 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity box="[543,715,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="0.535" valueMax="0.55" valueMin="0.52">0.52–0.55 mm</quantity>
; head width 1.4 4– 
<quantity box="[937,1045,1820,1845]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.50 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity box="[1260,1432,1820,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.33" metricValueMax="1.39" metricValueMin="1.27" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="1.33" valueMax="1.39" valueMin="1.27">1.27–1.39 mm</quantity>
; ocellus diameter 35.2–44.6 µm; interocellar distance 57.2–71.6 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1532,2024]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1437,151,1365]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1892,1917]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[275,385,1892,1917]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Tergite X elongate, rectangular in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[940,1036,1892,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 11a</figureCitation>
), expanded ventrad in lateral view, distal ventral margin with elongated, acutely triangular, paired tooth-like process, tooth medial subbasal margin with small medial tooth (
<figureCitation box="[436,534,1964,1989]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 11b</figureCitation>
). Pygofer with wide anterior apodeme; pygofer lobe with elongate ventroapical sclerotized process; about 14 macrosetae dorsomedially (
<figureCitation box="[814,977,1999,2024]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Figs 11a, 11b</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate length to width ratio 1.22–1.37 (n=5); laterobasal margin concave; apex broadly rounded; macrosetae in 2–3 irregular rows near apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,259,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). Valve transversely triangular, without anterior apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[956,1056,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with shaft elongate, sclerotized, straight in dorsal view, slightly curved in lateral view, apex with paired, acutely triangular tooth, directed ventrad, adpressed to shaft; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[767,924,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Figs 11d, 11e</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal paraphysis gracile, tubular, rightangled at base, apex acute, extending beyond apex of shaft (
<figureCitation box="[886,989,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11d</figureCitation>
). Style apophysis curvate, acuminate, elongated, curved dorsolaterally; preapical angle right-angled (
<figureCitation box="[872,968,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11f</figureCitation>
); positioned medially in subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[159,254,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11c</figureCitation>
). Connective with arms and stem of similar length (
<figureCitation box="[835,931,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[887,931,368,392]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.1" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="g" value="11.0">11g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Female</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[299,474,404,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity box="[655,821,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.825" metricValueMax="4.98" metricValueMin="4.67" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="4.825" valueMax="4.98" valueMin="4.67">4.67–4.98 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity box="[985,1150,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.41" valueMax="0.42" valueMin="0.4">0.40–0.42 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity box="[151,322,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.385" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.37">0.37–0.40 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity box="[543,715,439,464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="5.699999999999999" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.57" valueMin="0.53">0.53–0.57 mm</quantity>
; head width 1.5 
<quantity box="[908,1045,439,464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.29" metricValueMax="1.58" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="1.29" valueMax="1.58" valueMin="1.0">1–1.58 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
