. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[303,413,511,536]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Sternite VII posterior margin with wide, shallow, sinuous notch, medially with narrow, shallow V-shaped subnotch (
<figureCitation box="[474,571,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1404,1426]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,373,1367]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,373,1382]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11a–h. Discolopeus thigmacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Style, dorsally; g. Connective; h. Sternite VII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626833/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Fig. 11h</figureCitation>
). Valvifer 1 elongate, at least three times longer than wide (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1300,1422,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1852,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,481,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,481,1830]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7a–m. Discolopeus arctus n. gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e, f. Aedeagus, laterally, dorsally and ventrally respectively; g, h. Style, dorsally and laterally respectively; i. Connective, dorsally; j. Sternite VII; k, l. Valvifers 1, laterally, Clanwilliam and Nieuwoudtville respectively; m, profemur chaetotaxy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626825/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Figs 7k, 7l</figureCitation>
), posterior margin narrowly rounded, anterior margin narrow, membranously fused to other valvifer 1. Valvula 3 with 2–3 rows of macrosetae.
</paragraph>
